<HEADLINE>
India makes three changes for limited-overs series
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   WELLINGTON, New Zealand (AP) _ India made three changes Thursday
to its squad for the limited-overs section of its cricket tour of
New Zealand.
	   Veteran opener Navjot Sidhu, teenage offspinner Harbhajan Singh
and medium fast bowler Robin Singh Jr., will return home after the
third test which starts in Hamilton on Saturday.
	   They will be replaced by offspinners Hrishikesh Kanitkar and
Nikhil Chopra and allrounder Robin Singh Sr.
	   Kanitkar has been recalled to the Indian team after three years
away. Chopra played in Sharjah in September and is also a useful
batsman and Singh Sr., is a one-day specialist. (djp) 	   
