<SLUG> BC-Sports-Yachting-Sydney-Hobart </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Boats still finishing tragedy-marred race
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   HOBART, Australia (AP) _ Four weary yacht crews faced seeing in
the New Year at sea overnight Thursday night as they limped toward
the finish after surviving mountainous seas and gale-force winds in
the Sydney-to-Hobart race.
	   Four sailors were killed in the race and two others are missing
and presumed drowned.
	   Of the original 115 yachts which set out Dec. 26 on Sydney
Harbor, race officials expected a further 13 to get into Hobart on
Thursday, bringing to 42 the number of finishers in the
tragedy-marred race after the majority withdrew.
	   Liquid Asset, Allusive, Ocean Road and Misty are the four yachts
that will not finish until Friday. (djp) 	   
