to explore bringing those responsible for genocide to justice.
CAMBODIA-KHMER ROUGE. Has moved. By Chris Fontaine. AP Photos
PHN101-102, NY108.
	   NEW YORK _ Russia's failure to make a debt payment to commercial
banks worldwide this week could give banks an even stronger case
for denying crucial new loans to help rouse the country from its
crisis, analysts and economists say. US-RUSSIAN DEBT. Has moved. By
Maggie Jackson.
	   WASHINGTON _ Opening a rift with House prosecutors, Senate
Majority Leader Trent Lott suggests that President Bill Clinton's
impeachment trial be cut short unless an early preliminary vote
captured a two-thirds majority. Failure to attain that margin could
open the door to a censure. US-CLINTON-IMPEACHMENT. Lead has moved.
By Larry Margasak. AP Photo WX109.
	   WITH:
	   HILTON HEAD ISLAND, South Carolina _ With outlines of his State
of the Union address and fiscal 2000 budget tucked in his baggage,
President Bill Clinton begins a 48-hour, year's end escape from
Washington with an apparent focus on the future. US-CLINTON.
Expected by 1000 GMT. AP Photo AWH305.
	   WASHINGTON _ British Petroleum Co. and Amoco Corp. say they will
complete their dlrs 53 billion merger Thursday, after winning
regulatory approval from the Federal Trade Commission. US-BP-AMOCO
MERGER. Has moved. By Ted Bridis. AP Photos NY112,115.
	   UNITED NATIONS _ With full-scale war returning to Angola and the
downing of a U.N.-chartered plane there, the United Nations must
