<SLUG> BC-Sports-Baseball-Mariners-Mabry,0157 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Mariners sign Mabry to two-year deal
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SEATTLE (AP) _ The Seattle Mariners signed free agent
infielder-outfielder John Mabry to a two-year contract.
	   Mabry, 28, has spent his five-year major league career with the
St. Louis Cardinals. Last season, he played 46 games in left field,
38 at third base, 37 in right field, 16 at first base and pinch-hit
or pinch-ran in 31 games.
	   ``Mabry gives us a lot of flexibility,'' Mariners general
manager Woody Woodward said Wednesday.
	   Mabry hit .249 in 142 games with the Cardinals last season with
nine home runs and 46 RBIs. He has a .286 career average with 32
home runs and 200 RBIs in 544 games.
	   Mabry became a free agent on Dec. 21 when the Cardinals did not
offer him a 1999 contract. Mabry, who made dlrs 1.4 million last
season, would have been eligible for salary arbitration if the
Cardinals had kept him.
</TEXT>
