<SLUG> BC-China-US-Silk </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
China lifts silk exports restrictions to U.S.
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BEIJING (AP) _ China will lift restrictions on the export of
silk clothing to the United States on Friday, giving a boost to
what is already a billion dollar industry, official media said
Thursday.
	   Following a new agreement between China and the U.S., silk
garment exporters will no longer require an official export
license, the Xinhua News Agency said.
	   The move will help China improve its management of silk clothing
exports to the United States, simplify export procedures, cut the
cost of operations, and ``boost the growth of bilateral trade
relations,'' Xinhua reported.
	   Textiles and apparel are China's leading export products to the
U.S., with annual exports valued at dlrs 45 billion, Xinhua said.
The export of silk garments is valued at close to dlrs 2 billion a
year, it said. 	   
</TEXT>
