<HEADLINE>
Dollar mostly higher, gold up
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ The U.S. dollar was lower against the Japanese yen
but gained against other major currencies in European trading
Thursday morning. Gold rose.
	   Dollar rates compared with late Wednesday:
	   _113.60 Japanese yen, down from 114.83
	   _1.6753 German marks, up from 1.6740
	   _1.3776 Swiss francs, up from 1.3766
	   _5.6169 French francs, up from 5.6145
	   _1.8877 Dutch guilders, up/down from 1.8864
	   _1,658.10 Italian lire, up from 1,656.80
	   _1.5476 Canadian dollars, down from 1.5482
	   The British pound was quoted at dlrs 1.6570, down from dlrs
1.6667.
	   Gold dealers in London fixed a recommended price of dlrs 287.45
bid per troy ounce at midmorning, up from dlrs 287.40 late
Wednesday.
	   In Zurich the bid price was dlrs 287.50, up from dlrs 286.00.
	   Gold rose 70 cents in Hong Kong to dlrs 287.65.
	   The silver price in London was not available.
	   (rb)
