<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Israel-Population </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
At end of 1998, Israel's population 6.037 million
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   JERUSALEM (AP) _ Israel's population at the end of 1998 numbered
6.037 million, a 2.3 percent increase from a year ago, the Central
Bureau of Statistics said Thursday.
	   Of that number, 4.783 million, or 79.2 percent, were Jews, and
1.254 million, or 20.8 percent were non-Jews, including 901,000
Muslims and 129,000 Christians, the bureau said.
	   The number of immigrants to Israel fell by 14 percent in 1998 to
56,700 from 66,000 in 1997, the bureau said. The number of
immigrants from the former Soviet Union fell to 45,400 in 1998 from
54,600 in 1997.
	   More than 769,000 people emigrated to Israel from the former
Soviet Union from 1989 through 1998, accounting for some 85 percent
of all immigration during that period, the bureau said.
