<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Indonesia-ASEAN-EU </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ASEAN, European Union sign memorandum on economic cooperation
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) _ The Association of Southeast Asian
Nations and the European Union, on Thursday signed a memorandum of
understanding on a regional economic cooperation program.
	   Under the deal, the EU will contribute dlrs 6.12 million over
five years to a program designed to promote cooperation on product
standards, said the Jakarta-based ASEAN Secretariat.
	   ASEAN is a nine-member grouping that includes Indonesia,
Malaysia, Singapore, Thailand, the Philippines, Brunei, Laos,
Vietnam and Myanmar.
	   ``The signing of the (memorandum) reflects the ASEAN's strong
interest in continuing its cooperation with the EU in the field of
standards, quality and conformity assessment initiated almost a
decade ago,'' said a release from the secretariat.
	   It said the program will strengthen economic cooperation between
the two regional groupings and assist ASEAN in its efforts to
liberalize its economy.
	   It added that the cooperation will also promote international
trade through compatible standards and conformity assessment
procedures. Training provided under the program will help develop a
pool of ASEAN specialists on standards and conformity assessment,
it said.
</TEXT>
