<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Auto Racing-Dakar Rally,0184 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Prologue in southern Spanish city kicks off annual New Year grind
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; EDS: REPEATING to some lines to CORRECT slug to conform to style. &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   GRANADA, Spain (AP) _ With a 5-kilometer (3-mile) slosh around a
muddy army base, 90 cars, 163 motorcycles and 51 trucks roared the
21st Dakar Rally into life Thursday and began the annual gruelling
18-day trek.
	   The prologue set the order for Friday's first stage, a
520-kilometer leg from Granada southwest to the coastal town of
Algeciras.
	   Once the participants have crossed the narrow stretch of the
Mediterranean Sea separating Spain from North Africa, they are set
to begin their odyssey through Morocco, Mauritania, Mali and
Burkino Faso, before reaching Dakar, Senegal after 16 stages on
Jan. 17.
	   In the automobile category, defending champion Jean-Pierre
Fontenay and his Mitsubishi team start off as favorites.
	   The race looks more open for the motorcycles, particularly since
Frenchman Stephane Peterhansel, who won the title a record six
times, will be driving a car this year.
</TEXT>
