<HEADLINE>
Winter storms in Portugal cut off roads, close airport and ports
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LISBON, Portugal (AP) _ Snowstorms swept across areas of
northern Portugal on Thursday while high winds and driving rain
caused the closure of Faro international airport on the southern
coast.
	   Nine ports on the Atlantic coast were closed after waves reached
five meters (16.5 feet) high.
	   At Faro airport, four flights to Britain were canceled and three
incoming flights were diverted to the capital Lisbon and to
Seville, in neighboring Spain, when winds gusted at over 100
kilometers per hour (60 mph).
	   Officials said the winter storms could also disrupt air traffic
at Lisbon international airport.
	   Snowfall in the northeast cut off roads leading up to the Serra
da Estrela, Portugal's sole ski resort some 250 kilometers (155
miles) away from Lisbon, and a popular vacation destination.
	   (cp/bh/jt)
