<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Beardsley-Hartlepool </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Former England star joins third division club
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   HARTLEPOOL, England (AP) _ Former England international Peter
Beardsley joined third division Hartlepool United on Thursday.
	   The 37-year-old striker is likely to go straight into the squad
for Saturday's league clash with Cambridge United at Victoria Park.
	   Bearsdley is reuinted with Pool boss Mick Tait, who played with
him at Carlisle almost 20 years ago.
	   The former Newcastle, Liverpool and Everton player has not
started a game for several weeks after being released by Kevin
Keegan's Fulham.
	   ``It's a while since I actually started a game, but hopefully,
once I've got two or three under my belt, I'll be OK,'' he said.
``I was lucky enough to play with the boss at Carlisle and he
really looked after me then and took me under his wing.
	   ``This is a way to try to help repay him. When I saw Mick on
Sunday, he told me he was 41 when he packed in, and I'm only 38
next month, so I've got a few years to go yet.''
	   Pool has slipped to 21st place in the league after a disastrous
run of five successive defeats.
	   While Beardsley has played at the world's most famous venues in
some of the game's biggest matches, he has no qualms about running
out at Victoria Park in front of around 2,000 spectators.
	   ``About four or five weeks ago, I played in front of about 100
for the reserves, so that won't worry me,'' he said. `You don't
think about it, you just think about playing your game.''
	   (sw)	   
</TEXT>
