<SLUG> BC-Yugoslavia-Viagra </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Serbian menus: All you can eat, plus Viagra
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BELGRADE, Yugoslavia (AP) _ A Belgrade pizza restaurant is
offering a unique menu: All you can eat, plus the anti-impotence
drug Viagra. All for dlrs 50.
	   The owner, Miroslav Gajic, is more than happy with the sale.
``Viagra is a better invention than electricity,'' he was quoted as
saying in Thursday's independent daily Blic.
	   He said he sells ``between five and 30 such menus a day,'' and
that couples who eat them come back for more ``smiling.''
	   Gajic reportedly said the ``magic pill'' is a ``revolutionary
product which should be given a Nobel prize'' because it ``rises
from the dead.''
	   ``No wonder it was invented by weakling Americans,'' he said,
reflecting the belief of macho Serb males that they are the best in
sex.
	   Gajic said that his restaurant, named ``Grazia,'' is already
known as the ``Viagra Club.''
	   Viagra has been sold on the black market in Serbia and will be
available legally in pharmacies as of January.
	   (ds/dc)
</TEXT>
