<HEADLINE>
Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands from
the National Weather Service.
	   Showers will continue to move rapidly across Puerto Rico during
the early afternoon hours, but very dry air behind these showers
will ensure mostly sunny skies and ideal conditions for outdoor
activities over the U.S. Virgin Islands and Puerto Rico for most of
the afternoon.
	   Marine conditions over our coastal waters have improved
considerably as the winds and seas continue to diminish.
	   However, mariners are advised to exercise caution while
navigating over the offshore waters of the Atlantic and Caribbean.
	   San Juan and the northern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers. High
around 85. Wind east 10 to 15 mph.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers.
Low 70 to 75. Wind light southeast.
	   New Year's Day... Partly cloudy. A 20 percent chance of showers.
High 80 to 85. Wind east 10 to 15 mph.
	   Remainder of New Year's Weekend... Partly cloudy. Scattered
showers. Low 70 to 75. High 80 to 85.
	   Eastern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Partly cloudy with 30 percent chance of showers. High
80 to 85. Wind east 10 to 15 mph.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers.
Low 70 to 75. Wind east 5 to 10 mph.
	   New Year's Day... Partly cloudy with a 20 percent chance of
showers. High 80 to 85. Wind east 10 to 15 mph.
	   Remainder of New Year's Weekend... Partly cloudy. Scattered
showers. Low 70 to 75. High 80 to 85.
	   Ponce and the southern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Partly cloudy with a 20 percent chance of showers...
Mainly east. High 85 to 90. Wind southeast 10 to 15 mph.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers.
Low around 70. Wind light from the northeast.
	   New Year's Day... Partly cloudy with a 20 percent chance of
showers. High around 85. Wind southeast 10 to 15 mph.
	   Remainder of New Year's Weekend... Partly cloudy. Widely
scattered showers. Low around 70. High around 85.
	   Mayaguez and the western sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Mostly sunny in the morning. Partly cloudy afternoon
with a 30 percent chance of showers. High 85 to 90. Wind east 10 to
15 mph, except variable less than 10 mph along the west coast in
the afternoon.
	   Tonight... Generally fair. Low 65 to 70. Wind light from the
east.
	   New Year's Day... Sunny in the morning. Partly cloudy in the
afternoon with a 20 percent chance of showers. High around 85. Wind
east 10 to 15 mph, except for a variable wind less than 10 mph
along the west coast in the afternoon.
	   Remainder of New Year's Weekend... Partly cloudy days. Mostly
clear nights. Scattered afternoon showers. Low around 70. High
around 85.
	   Interior sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers. High
from near 70 in the mountains to near 85 in lower elevations. Wind
east 10 to 15 mph.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy east with a 20 percent chance of
showers. Generally fair west. Low 60 to 70. Wind east 5 to 10 mph.
	   New Year's Day... Partly cloudy with a 20 percent chance of
showers. High of 70 in the mountains, 85 in lower valleys. Wind
east 10 to 15 mph.
	   Remainder of New Year's Weekend... Partly cloudy. Scattered
showers. Low 70 to 75. High of 70 in the mountains, 85 in lower
valleys.
	   St. Thomas, St. John and the Adjacent Islands-St. Croix:
	   Today... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers,
mainly in the morning. High around 85. Wind east 10 to 15 mph.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers.
Low 70 to 75. Wind east 5 to 10 mph.
	   New Year's Day... Partly cloudy. A 20 percent chance of showers.
High around 85. Wind east 10 to 15 mph.
	   Remainder of New Year's Weekend... Partly cloudy. Scattered
showers. Low 70 to 75. High 80 to 85.
	   Atlantic waters north and northeast of Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands:
	   Small craft should exercise caution.
	   This afternoon... Wind east to southeast around 15 kt. Near
shore seas 3 to 4 ft. Offshore 4 to 6 ft. Widely scattered showers.
	   Tonight... Wind east 10 to 15 kt. Near shore seas 3 to 4 ft.
Offshore seas 4 to 6 ft. Widely scattered showers.
	   Friday... Wind east around 15 kt. Near shore seas 3 to 4 ft.
Offshore seas 4 to 6 ft. Widely scattered showers.
	   Caribbean waters south and southeast of Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands:
	   Small craft should exercise caution.
	   This afternoon... Wind east to southeast around 15 kt. Near
shore seas 3 to 4 ft. Offshore seas 4 to 6 ft. Widely scattered
showers.
	   Tonight... Wind east 10 to 15 kt. Near shore seas 3 to 4 ft.
Offshore seas 4 to 6 ft. Widely scattered showers.
	   Friday... Wind east around 15 kt. Near shore seas 3 to 4 ft.
Offshore seas 4 to 6 ft. Widely scattered showers.
	   Near shore waters of western Puerto Rico:
	   This afternoon... Wind east to southeast 10 to 15 kt. Seas 2 to
4 ft. Isolated showers.
	   Tonight... Wind east around 10 kt. Seas 2 ft. Isolated showers.
	   Friday... Wind east 10 to 15 kt. Seas 2 to 4 ft. Isolated
showers.
	   Outlook for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands waters:
	   Friday night through Monday... Wind east increasing to around 20
kt. Seas up to 7 ft.
