<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Basketball-Del Negro-Bologna </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Spurs guard Vinny Del Negro looks headed to Italy
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BOLOGNA, Italy (AP) _ San Antonio Spurs guard Vinny Del Negro is
close to signing a deal with Fortitudo Bologna of the Italian
basketball league, team officials say.
	   Del Negro, who has dual American-Italian nationality and played
previously in Italy in the early '90s, is expected to arrive in
Bologna on Sunday to complete the move.
	   Under the proposed contract, Del Negro could return to the NBA
if the lockout ends.
	   The deadline for registering players for Euro League play is
Monday. Del Negro would be eligible to play against CSKA Moscow
next Thursday.
	   The Italian sports daily Gazzetta dello Sport said the deal
being worked out with Del Negro's agent, Jack Marin, has an escape
clause allowing the player to return to the NBA if the owners and
players end their labor dispute.
	   Under the terms of the proposed contract, Del Negro is required
to stay with the Italian club for a minimum of 30-40 days, a period
encompassing about 10 games.
	   The NBA lockout has been in effect for almost six months, and
the first three months of the season have already been scrapped.
	   Commissioner David Stern says he'll recommend the entire season
be canceled if there's no agreement with players by next Thursday.
	   ``Even if he leaves, Vinny will have played for us for
practically free,'' Fortitudo administrator Massimo Gambini said.
``The contract, apart from the clauses, runs to June 1999 and has
an option for next season. If Del Negro wants to stay, we are ready
to keep him for the future.''
	   Del Negro won an Italian league championship with Benetton
Treviso in 1992.
	   He was one of the Spurs' main outside shooting threats last
season. The Spurs advanced to the Western Conference semifinals
before losing to Utah 4-1.
	   Del Negro would join some other NBA players who have already
signed with European teams.
	   Center Arvydas Sabonis of the Portland Trail Blazers has joined
Lithuania's Zalgiras Vilnius, and Vlade Divac, who played with the
Charlotte Hornets last season, is with Red Star Belgrade. Those two
teams will meet in a Euro League game in Belgrade on Jan. 7.
	   In addition, Spanish club Real Madrid is hoping to sign Rik
Smits of the Indiana Pacers and Zyrdrunas Ilgauskus of the
Cleveland Cavaliers.
	   (sw) 	   
</TEXT>
