<SLUG> BC-France-Homeless Protest </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
About 100 homeless people help themselves at Galeries Lafayette
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PARIS (AP) _ About 100 homeless people helped themselves without
paying to gourmet food Thursday in the upscale Galeries Lafayette
department store in Paris.
	   The homeless protesters stocked up and then left the store
pushing about 20 grocery carts full of goodies.
	   Galeries Lafayette management proposed that the protesters take
what they needed to provide a New Year's feast for about 100 people
after the group entered the store.
	   The protesters loaded up on champagne, wine, chocolate, pizza,
smoked salmon and baby formula before taking their carts into the
subway.
	   France's unemployment rate is currently 11.5 percent, and
jobless people frequently stage protests, especially at the end of
the year before the Christmas and New Year holidays.
	   (parf-dgs) 	   
</TEXT>
