<SLUG> BC-Algeria </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Three people killed, seven wounded in new violence in Algeria
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PARIS (AP) _ Three people were killed and seven others wounded
in new violence in Algeria, newspapers reported Thursday.
	   According to the Liberte daily, two adolescents were killed and
three others wounded Wednesday at a fake road block set up by an
armed group near Blida, about 50 kilometers (31 miles) south of
Algiers.
	   The victims had been shot and were found in a bus that had been
stopped by an explosion from a homemade bomb, the newspaper
reported.
	   In another violent incident, an armed group attacked a bus
Monday evening near Boumerdes, a town about 50 kilometers (31
miles) east of Algiers, the Le Matin newspaper reported. One person
was killed and four others were wounded, the daily said.
	   An estimated 75,000 people have been killed since the start of
Algeria's insurgency, triggered by an army decision to cancel
elections the Islamic Salvation Front was set to win in 1992.
	   (parf-dgs)	   
