<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Keller Future </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Status of U.S. goalkeeper uncertain with Leicester
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LEICESTER, England (AP) _ U.S. goalkeeper Kasey Keller's future
at Premier League club Leicester remains uncertain heading into the
new year.
	   Keller has declined to sign a new contract offered by manager
Martin O'Neill earlier this season.
	   With his current contract expiring at the end of the season,
Keller is free to talk to other clubs starting Jan. 1. He is
eligible to leave Leicester on a free transfer next summer.
	   ``It is true that from tomorrow I can technically look around
for a new club _ but I am not actively looking for a move,'' Keller
said Thursday. ``As far as I am concerned I am playing here, with
Leicester City, at present and we will have to see what happens.
	   ``I am expecting to still have talks with the manager about a
new contract here and that's how things stand at the moment.''
	   O'Neill said he had not been contacted by any club about Keller.
	   (sw)	   
</TEXT>
