<HEADLINE>
Storm knocks down wall in Seville, killing four
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SEVILLE, Spain (AP) _ Part of a building facade crumbled during
a storm Thursday, killing four people waiting at a bus stop, police
said.
	   Winds gusting at up to 80 kilometers per hour (50 mph) sent
chunks of wall tumbling from a disused building that used to house
a market, police said.
	   The debris crushed a bus stop shelter, killing four people and
injuring at least one, Seville police said.
	   The storm was part of a New Year's Eve weather system whipping
up strong winds and torrential rain in much of Spain.
	   Elsewhere in Seville and the surrounding province, the storm
knocked down trees and triggered electrical blackouts, officials
said
	   (dw)
