w2224 &Cx1f; wstm-
r i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-APTNOutlook     12-31 0930
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-APTN Outlook,0949 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>

</HEADLINE>
----
 &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  APTN'S 1800 GMT Outlook for Thursday December 31 1998  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC; 
----
For Planner/Newsdesk use stories expected to move in the next 12
hours. All times in GMT.
----
EXPECTED:  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC; 
----
NEW YEAR CELEBRATIONS -
----
As midnight strikes and 1999 begins, we have coverage of
celebrations from around the world starting in Australia, (First run
Europe Update 1310) Japan and Hong Kong. (First run F-l-a-s-h 1800)
----
EUROPE -
- from Russia we will have an address from the Patriarch Alexei II,
a speech from Yeltsin (speech embargoed until 2100 and is no access
Russia) as well as celebrations from Red Square (2200)
- from London the traditional shots from Trafalgar Square at 0000
GMT;
- from Paris - the end of year address from Chirac - (after 1900)
- from Frankfurt  -countdown on the millennium clock and euro signs
- and later L-I-V-E coverage from Times Square in the U-S at 0500.
-----
WORLD: EURO - A wrap of UK: Euro which examines the impact it will
have in Britain even though it remains outside the single currency,
with  Italy: Euro which has reactions to someone trying out a new
euro cheque book on some Italian businesses as well as a soundbite
from an economist at Merrill Lynch in Washington. (Wrap first run
Asia Pacific Early 1945 )
-----
FRANCE: EURO - Shots from the Banque Populaire with a huge euro coin
and shots of the bank staff working on the changeover to euros on
their computers as well as an interview with the head of BNP's
computer section plus shots from the Bourse.  (Expected First run
North America 2030 )
----
LUXEMBOURG: EURO - The special publication of the official journal
with the new rates at which the currencies of 11 EU nations will be
locked to form a new single currency. (After 1900)
-----
ITALY POPE - The Pope's final worship for 1998 at St. Ignazio di
Loyala Church where he gives thanks for the past year. (Expected
First run F-l-a-s-h 1800)
-----
JAPAN: OBUCHI - The New Year's address from Prime Minister Obuchi
which includes reaction to the euro - this is embargoed until 2000
GMT. (No access Japan) (Expected F-l-a-s-h at 1800)
-----
ANGOLA: UN SEARCH- Rescuers still haven't been able to get to the
crash site but the UN Special Representative for Angola, Issa
Diallo, said relatives should try not to be too anxious. The item
also has Holden Roberto, leader of the Angolan National Liberation
Front, saying he's ashamed the fighting is continuing preventing a
rescue. (Expected F-l-a-s-h 1800)
----
YEMEN: HOSTAGES 2 - We will be updating our running package with the
news conference from the Interior Minister and the UK consul.
(timing TBA) This will be added to the shots of the German hostages
at the German embassy in Sana'a as well as shots inside the morgue
of the coffins of three of those killed. (First run Europe Update
1245)
-----
LIBYA: DEMAND - Libya wants the United States to hand over nine
officials of the Reagan administration -- one of them dead -- to
face charges in connection with US air raids on Libya in 1986. We
have the statement from the Libyan attorney-general. (First run
North America Update 1930)
-----
US: SWIM - A midwinter's dip for New Year's Eve revellers in New
York.   (Expected First run North America 2030 )
-----
RUNNING &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC; 
-----
EURO LAUNCH:
-----
BRUSSELS: EURO WRAP - The European Commission has agreed on the
irreversible rates at which the currencies of 11 EU nations will be
locked to form a new single currency. We have soundbites from
Jacques Santer, EU Commission President as well as European Central
Bank chief Wim Duisenberg as well as the official signing ceremony
and release of balloons to celebrate. (First run Europe Late 1600)
-----
EURO: POLITICS - The item shows  Dominique Strauss-Kahn, the French
Finance Minister talking about the Euro against the US dollar and
about the need for Duisenberg to honour his commitment to step down
to make way for the candidate France had backed for the post. (First
run Europe Late 1600)
----
RUSSIA: SPACE Astronauts on board the space shuttle Mir celebrate
New Year in orbit. (First run Europe Update 1310)
----
SAFRICA MANDELA - 1999 marks the year that Nelson Mandela hands over power
to his deputy, Thabo Mbeki. Mandela talks about the problems still
facing South Africa in his annual New Year address.
Please note - his speech is  EMBARGOED UNTIL 1800 GMT.
(First run Europe Update 1245)
------
ISRAEL: EMBASSY - The US ambassador closed the US
Embassy in Tel Aviv after receiving "credible" threats. We see extra
Israeli police posted outside the Mediterranean beachfront building
following the closure. (First run The Americas 1000)
-----
IRAQ: WRAP -  Thousands of children take part in a demonstration
organised by the Italian charity Bridge to Baghdad calling for an
end to sanctions as women pray in the mosques on Thanksgiving day.
(First run Europe Morning 0900) Wrapped into this was Pentagon Video
of laser guided bombs being released from American F-16 fighter
jets. First Run 0300g F-L-A-S-H - 31 Dec)
-----
UK: BLOOD SON - The first television pictures of the baby born to
Diane Blood, the young widow who fought for nearly three years for
the right to have her late husband's child using his sperm. (First
run Europe Late 1600)
-----
