w2232 &Cx1f; wstm-
r i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Greece-Immigrants-Sin 2ndLd-Writethru   12-31 0312
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Greece-Immigrants-Sinking, 2nd Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Immigrants drown and reported missing after boat sinks
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: LEADS throughout. UPDATES adding details of rescue, survivors
and arrests. No pickup.

<TEXT>
	   ATHENS, Greece (AP) _ Rescue teams interrupted a search for
possible survivors late Thursday after a boat carrying illegal
immigrants sank in the eastern Aegean Sea, authorities said.
	   At least two people drowned and 10 others were reported missing
when the wooden vessel took on water and sank in rough seas, the
merchant marine ministry said.
	   Ships in the area and port authority vessels rescued two Greek
sailors, one Yugoslav and 21 men from Pakistan, India, Rwanda and
Iraq who had been on board the 17-meter (56-foot) Italian-flagged
Mustang.
	   The search, aided by a helicopter, will resume early Friday.
	   News reports said the two Greek sailors and the Yugoslav man had
been arrested to face charges of migrant smuggling. Survivors told
local media they had each agreed to pay dlrs 1,500 to be
transported from the Turkish coast to Greece.
	   The identity and nationality of the two victims were not known.
Survivors where hospitalized on the nearby island of Kos, all in
good condition.
	   A distress signal was issued from the boat at around 5:30 a.m.
(0330 GMT) before it sank off the island of Nissiros, near the
Turkish coast and about 320 kilometers (200 miles) southeast of
Athens, authorities said.
	   Tens of thousands of illegal immigrants, mostly Iraqi Kurds,
attempt each year to cross from the Turkish coast to nearby Greek
islands. Many are arrested and deported, but others apply for
asylum in Greece and are taken to refugee camps while their
applications are processed.
	   Hundreds find work clandestinely in Greece or move on to Italy
to make their way to other European countries.
	   (dg-eb-bm) 	   
</TEXT>
(PROFILE
(WS SL:BC-Greece-Immigrants-Sinking, 2nd Ld-Writethru; CT:i; 
(REG:EURO;)
(REG:BRIT;)
(REG:SCAN;)
(REG:ENGL;)
(REG:MEST;)
