<SLUG> BC-France-Obit-Deschamps </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Hubert Deschamps, well-known French supporting actor dies at 75
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PARIS (AP) _ Hubert Deschamps, a popular French actor best known
for supporting roles in dozens of films, has died, his family said
Thursday. He was 75.
	   Deschamps came to film after studying fine arts and performing
in cabarets. He played in such movies as ``Zazie in the Metro'' by
Louis Malle and ``Tender Chicken'' by Phillipe de Broca.
	   Deschamps died Wednesday, the family said.
	   The funeral was to be held Monday, according to French radio.
	   (parf-dgs) 	   
</TEXT>
