<HEADLINE>
Flash floods wreak havoc on northern Israel
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   JERUSALEM (AP) _ After months of drought, rain flooded northern
Israel Thursday, destroying property and forcing thousands of
residents to evacuate.
	   Israel television said 20 centimeters (8 inches) of rain fell on
the Carmel region throughout the day.
	   In the southern Israeli town of Ashkelon, 59 foreign workers
from Korea and Romania were stranded on a pier after huge waves
struck their houseboat away from the pier, Israel's army radio
said. While no one was injured, the workers were to stay on the
pier until dawn after darkness and harsh weather conditions
suspended rescue efforts.
	   By nightfall, the rain has mostly stopped and residents were
starting to return to their homes.
