<HEADLINE>
Barcelona driver swerves onto sidewalk, injuring 13 people
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BARCELONA, Spain (AP) _ A driver lost control of his car because
of a coughing fit and ran into pedestrians waiting at an
intersection in downtown Barcelona on Thursday, injuring 13, police
said.
	   Police told the state-run agency Efe that none of the 13 had
life-threatening injuries.
	   The driver swerved onto a sidewalk, hitting people, two
motorcycles, a traffic light and a trash bin before coming to a
stop, witness said.
	   He told police he lost control of the car because of a coughing
fit.
