<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Virgin Islands-Esso,0121 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Esso Virgin Islands settles environmental lawsuit
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   CHRISTIANSTED, U.S. Virgin Islands (AP) _ Esso Virgin Islands
Inc., the distributor of Exxon gasoline in the U.S. territory, has
settled a federal lawsuit over environmental standards.
	   U.S. Attorney James A. Hurd, Jr. said the company agreed to pay
dlrs 294,200 and improve methods for detecting gasoline leaks at
its bulk storage tanks at Estate Lindberg on St. Thomas.
	   The company agreed to use new procedures for monitoring the
loading of tank trucks and conduct monthly inspections for leaks.
The U.S. Environmental Protection Agency is charged with making
sure the company abides by the agreement.
</TEXT>
