<HEADLINE>
Palestinian minister says he hopes state will come through talks
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with Arafat quote, 3rd graf &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   JERUSALEM (AP) _ A top Palestinian official said Thursday that
he expected a Palestinian state to be formed in 1999, but that he
hoped it would be as a result of negotiations with Israel.
	   Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat has made contradictory
statements in recent months about whether he would unilaterally
declare a state on May 4, the deadline for reaching a permanent
Israeli-Palestinian peace agreement.
	   On Thursday, Arafat called upon supporters to ``continue until
we achieve a Palestinian state with its capital in holy
Jerusalem.''
