<TEXT>
	   WORLD AT 0000 GMT
	    &UR; NEW:
	   _IRAQ-STRUGGLING FAMILIES. Families struggle to make ends meet.
	   _ISRAEL-PALESTINIANS. Arafat renews vow for statehood, calls on
Israelis to make peace.
	   _US-BALLOON QUEST-SCIENCE. Australia balloon crew to soar with
weather study.
 &UR; MAIN SPOT NEWS:
	   BRUSSELS, Belgium _ The euro is officially the common currency
of 11 European countries, creating a powerful new economic force
and fulfilling the postwar unity dreams of nations whose divisions
twice this century dragged the planet into its bloodiest wars. THE
EURO. RECAP expected by 0300 GMT. By Paul Ames. AP Photos
BRU101-110,114, FRA103,105, PAR101-103. AP Graphics EURO PROFILE,
EURO CHRONO, EURO CURRENCY, EU CENTRAL BANKS, EURO OUTSIDERS.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _THE EURO-THE OTHERS _ Single currency reaches beyond the
founding 11 nations.
	   MOSCOW _ The Russian government says the ruble's value dropped
almost 70 percent over the last four months against the dollar. And
it says that the inflation rate reached 84.4 percent in 1998.
RUSSIA-ECONOMY. Has moved. By Judith Ingram.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _US-ECONOMY-NEW YEAR _ It may be a new year but the economic
forecast for 1999 has an old familiar ring. AP Photos NYR116-117.
	   SIHANOUKVILLE, Cambodia _ Two former Khmer Rouge leaders and
their well-dressed wives, children and grandchildren get a
government-arranged pleasure tour of the country they once brutally
ruled. CAMBODIA-KHMER ROUGE. Expected by 0800 GMT. By Ker Munthit.
	   UNITED NATIONS _ The Security Council holds an emergency meeting
to demand the Angolan government and particularly UNITA rebels let
a U.N. team reach the site of a downed U.N.-chartered plane
carrying 14 people. UN-ANGOLA. Has moved.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _ANGOLA _ Government offers to cooperate in reaching site of
downed U.N. plane.
	   BAGHDAD, Iraq _ Food that Iraq has bought under a U.N. program
has eased the hardship of eight years of trade sanctions. But
Iraqis like Ceceel George, who is struggling to feed the nine
hungry mouths in her house, say it does not meet their basic needs.
IRAQ-STRUGGLING FAMILIES. Expected by 0300 GMT. By Louis Meixler.
AP Photos BAG106-107.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _IRAQ _ Iraqi official says there will be no letup in Iraq's
``battle against aggression.''
	   _US-IRAQ-TARGETS _ Saddam Hussein's anti-aircraft missiles make
difficult targets.
	   FREETOWN, Sierra Leone _ Heavy shelling rocks the hills south of
the Sierra Leone capital as West African troops protecting the
country's elected president exchange artillery fire with
insurgents. SIERRA LEONE. Has moved.
	   NEW YORK _ The world offers a high-spirited welcome to the last
year of the second millennium, with fireworks in Scotland,
pilgrimages to shrines and temples in Asia, and the annual descent
of a 500-pound (227-kilo) aluminum ball in New York. NEW YEAR'S
WORLD ROUNDUP. RECAP expected by 0300 GMT. By Robert Seely. AP
Photos MOSB101, KL101, TOK104-106, SYD101-102, HK101-102,
ATH101-102.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _POPE-NEW YEAR'S EVE _ Pope John Paul II counts down to 2000 _
not 1999 _ on his New Year's Eve, reminding Rome and the Roman
Catholic Church they have one year left to get ready for
Christianity's millennium jubilee. AP Photos ROM101-103.
	   GAZA CITY, Gaza Strip _ Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat calls
upon the Israeli people to work together for peace and renewed his
pledge to build a Palestinian state. ISRAEL-PALESTINIANS. Has
moved. By Ibrahim Barzak.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _ISRAEL-LEBANON _ Netanyahu says Israel will attack Lebanon if
hit by rockets. AP Photos XKIR101-103.
	   _ISRAEL-UNFRIENDLY FIRE _ Hasty blame in friendly fire incident
angers Israelis.
	   MEXICO CITY _ For the second straight year, a split over the
budget has allowed the ruling Insitutional Revolutionary Party to
push through most of its own proposal, despite its eroding
influence in Congress. MEXICO-POWERFUL PRI. Has moved. By Mark
Stevenson. AP Photo MO101.
	   WASHINGTON _ Researchers have discovered that tots as tiny as 7
months old understand how words go together to form sentences _ a
finding that may prove useful in the diagnosis and treatment of
language disorders. US-SCI-LITTLE LEARNERS. Has moved. By Paul
Recer.
	   ALBUQUERQUE, New Mexico _ The crew of Saturday's planned liftoff
of the Team RE/MAX balloon has volunteered to take six different
scientific payloads to analyze weather and other conditions from
more than twenty miles above the Earth's surface. US-BALLOON
QUEST-SCIENCE. Expected by 0300 GMT. By Troy Goodman. AP Photo
WXS802.
	   LOOKING AHEAD: On Saturday, a U.S.-Australian team is slated to
try again to lift off the giant balloon they want to fly around the
world.
 &UR; FEATURES:
	   CHIANG MAI, Thailand _ Rebel groups in Myanmar brace for
government offensives, which tend to escalate after the rainy
season stops and roads leading to the eastern border dry out.
FEA-MYANMAR-REBEL ARMIES. To move as wire time permits. By Don
Pathan. AP Photo BK101.
	   MANAMA, Bahrain _ Once a farming and fishing country, Bahrain
now has international banks, high-rise buildings and fast-food
restaurants. It's startling to see how much life has changed. A new
world was made by oil, and now it is being remade as the oil runs
out. FEA-BAHRAIN-CHANGED SOCIETY. To move as wire time permits. By
Adnan Malik. AP Photo NY332.
	   Also Moving: US-TOP TEN _ Weekly charts for the best-selling
recorded music in the United States.
	   YOUR QUERIES: The Associated Press World Service editors in
charge are Kim Gamel and Sau Chan. Suggestions and story requests
to The Associated Press World Service are welcome. Contact your
local AP bureau or the AP International Desk in New York, telephone
(1) 212-621-1650, fax (1) 212-621-5449.
