<HEADLINE>
United States 5, Canada 2
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   WINNIPEG, Manitoba (AP) _ Brian Gionta scored two goals Thursday
as the United States beat Canada 5-2 for its first win in four
games at the world junior hockey championship.
	   Scott Gomez added a goal and two assists for the United States,
which beat Canada for the second straight year at the world
tournament. Ryan Murphy and William Heisten also scored.
	   The U.S. had lost its first three games going into the final day
of the round robin on Thursday and had no hope of making the
playoffs. But the Americans did prevent Canada from finishing in
first place in Pool A and getting a bye in the playoff round.
	   The Canadians will now meet Kazakhstan, the third-place team in
Pool B, on Saturday in the quarterfinal.
	   Adam Mair and Daniel Tkaczuk scored for Canada against U.S.
goaltender Joe Blackburn, who stopped 36 shots.
	   In Thursday's other games, Sweden beat Kazakhstan 11-4 and
Russia stopped Switzerland 6-0.
</TEXT>
