<HEADLINE>
APTN 0100 GMT Outlook
</HEADLINE>

----
 &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  APTN'S 0100 Outlook for Friday January 1 1999  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC; 
----
For Planner/Newsdesk use stories expected to move in the next 12
hours. All times in GMT.
----
EXPECTED:  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC; 
----
US: TIMES SQUARE - L-I-V-E coverage from New York of the annual
dropping of the ball from One Times Square.
(Live at 0500 gmt)
-----
UK: NEW YEAR -  Updates earlier wrap with Edinburgh Castle
Fireworks.
 (First Expected Run at 0130 Flash)
----
UN: ANGOLA - The U-N Security Council voted unanimously to pass a
resolution that requests access to the crash site by a U-N
team, and set a deadline of January 11th for compliance. (First Run
0400 Europe Early)
-----
GABON: PRESIDENT - In his first interview for 40 years, the
Gabonese President talks about British investments.
(First Run 0400 Europe Early)
-----
SOUTH AFRICA: CONDOM -  South Africa's Department of Health has
introduced a new quality control system in reaction to a report that
millions of substandard condoms were imported into the country.
(First Run 0400 Europe Early)
------
CHINA: WINTER TONICS - Feature on Chinese Winter Tonics.
(First Run 0400 Europe Early)
------
EURO : WRAP - Updates previous wraps with the special publication of
the official journal with new rates at which the currencies of 11 EU
nations which will be locked to form a new single currency with
Jacques santer in attendance. Package includes launch from Thursday,
printing of Euro Traveller Cheques, shots of the Euro coin,
and reaction from the Dutch European Central Bank chief Wim
Duisenberg over the French furore over whether he will step down
after completing half his term.
(First Run 0400 Europe Early)
------

RUNNING &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC; 
-----
MOSCOW: NEW YEAR - Colorful celebrations from Red Square in the
bitter cold to usher in the new year. (First Run at 2300
Australia/NZ)
-----
GERMANY: NEW YEAR/EURO CLOCK - From Frankfurt, APTN has the
countdown on the millennium clock and euro signs as well as general
new year merriment. (First Run at 0050 Flash)
----
UK: NEW YEAR -  Celebrations from Trafalgar Square .
 (First Run at 0050 Flash)
----
WORLD: NEW YEAR - APTN wraps new year celebrations from Australia,
Japan and Hong Kong.
(First Run at 1930 Lat Am)
------
ITALY POPE - The pope's final worship for 1998 at St. Ignazio di
Loyala Church where he gives thanks for the past year. (First run
F-l-a-s-h 1800)
-----
JAPAN: OBUCHI - The New Year's address from Prime Minister Keizo Obuchi
which includes reaction to the euro - this is embargoed until 2000
GMT. (No access Japan) (First Run at F-l-a-s-h at 1800)
-----
ANGOLA: UN SEARCH- Rescuers still haven't been able to get to the
crash site but the U-N Special Representative for Angola, Issa
Diallo said relatives should try not to be too anxious. The item
also has Holden Roberto, leader of the Angolan National Liberation
Front saying he's ashamed the fighting is continuing preventing a
rescue.
(First Run at F-l-a-s-h at 1800)
-----
LIBYA: DEMAND - Libya wants the United States to hand over nine
officials of U.S. President Ronald Reagan's administration -- one of them dead -- to
face charges in connection with U-S air raids on Libya in 1986. We
have the statement from the Libyan attorney-general. (First run
North America Update 1930)
-----
US: SWIM - A midwinter's dip for New Year's Eve revellers in New
York.   (First run Asia Pacific Early 1945 )
-----

